      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To calculate your inventory turnover ratio, divide your cost of goods sold (COGS) by your average inventory value for the period. This number tells you how many times a year your boutique sells and replaces its stock, so a higher ratio generally indicates strong sales velocity compared to competitors in the same niche. You should aim for a ratio that keeps your shelves fresh but cares not to sacrifice your least popular items entirely when setting your sales strategy.",
